entries.s_43: He's in there. My husband, Vryim. They took him. They said he knew things about their organization that he shouldn't know. But he didn't. He's just a vehicle repairman. They said they were going to use him in their experiments. What does that mean? Oh, Vryim, I miss you. I want you back.
entries.s_45: I'm sorry, but there's nothing I can do.
entries.s_46: You will? Oh, thank you! Please, hurry. Find him.
entries.s_47: I know. There's nothing anyone can do. He's lost to me. Lost.
entries.s_48: Vryim? He's dead? No. Oh, but I think I knew. I think I felt something when he died. Something that drew me out of the city to this place. I just didn't understand until now. Oh, Vryim. I'll miss you.
entries.s_49: My husband is somewhere within inside that place. Please find him and bring him home safely.
